      "title": "PACT: Anonymous Credentials for the Web – Mozilla Hacks",
      "url": "https://hacks.mozilla.org/2026/06/pact-anonymous-credentials-for-the-web/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/6pdyiy",
      "score": 2,
      "comments": 0,
      "author": "brn",
      "published": "2026-07-17T06:01:54Z",
      "bullets": [
        "PACT uses blind signatures and VOPRF to verify user attributes, like humanness, without enabling cross-site tracking or deanonymization.",
        "Aligned with IETF Privacy Pass, PACT offers a cryptographically secure, privacy-preserving alternative to CAPTCHAs and tracking cookies.",
        "It prevents token double-spending while ensuring unlinkability by cryptographically separating the token issuer from the verifying origin server."
      ]
    },
